invention: I would like to build an app, that allows pharmacists in homeinfusion to double check bar codes. Unlike amazon where each individual item has a specific barcode. In home infusion, each patient gets a barcode, where all items going to that patient gets the same barcode. This makes it easy to mix up orders, especially when patients have the same medicine. The app would use an API to scan two bar codes and compare them. This app could even scan all of a patients item, and see if there are any deviations. If I had all the resources, I would make some sort of tracker in each package, that way as the packages roll out the door, we could make note of the item. This would make our health care just a bit more secure and more efficient.
